    {"instruction": "Why is Oops All Spells favored against Lands?", "input": "", "output": "Lands operates entirely at sorcery speed through land abilities. It has no counterspells, no instant-speed graveyard hate in the maindeck, and no way to interact with a combo that wins by milling a library and casting Thassa's Oracle. Lands' strengths (Wasteland, Maze of Ith, Punishing Fire) are all irrelevant against Oops. The only interaction is sideboard Bojuka Bog (found by Crop Rotation) or Surgical Extraction, which requires the Oops player to fill the graveyard first."},
